FT  15 DEC 93 / The path to peace
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
February 1993: secret contacts between British government and provisional
leadership begin with provisional message - since denied - saying conflict
is over
April: Hume and Adams talks begin in secret
July: Reynolds sends draft of possible joint peace declaration to London
September: Mayhew seeks to relaunch stalled talks
October 29: Major and Reynolds set out six guiding principles for settlement
November 4: Hume tells Major there could be peace in a week if his
initiative with Adams is embraced
November 5: British government sets out secret proposals for meeting with
provisionals
November 15: Adams publicly claims contact with government
December 3: Major and Reynolds hold seven-hour talks in Dublin
December 10: Major and Reynolds meet for an hour at European council summit
in Brussels
December 15: Reynolds in London to agree joint declaration
