FT  14 DEC 93 / World Commodities Prices: Tea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Tea Broker's Association reports; landed good general demand. Coloury
Assams were well supported at fully firm rates but poor types were again
difficult of sale. Brightest liquoring and better medium East Africans were
mainly dearer by 3 to 8p, others were generally fully firm except the
plainest. Ceylons sold well at fully firm rates although plainer sorts
drifted lower. Offshore fair demand with brighter Kenyas tending dearer,
Ceylons fully firm. Plainer Kenyas met less demand at lower levels.
Quotations: quality 220p/kg, good medium 145p/kg medium 112p/kg low medium
98p/kg. The highest price realised this week was 256 for a Rwanda pd.
