<HEADLINE>
FT  14 DEC 93 / International Company News: Demand for Taiwanese insurer
issue
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TAIPEI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Taiwan government's offer of 18m shares of Chung Kuo Insurance was fully
subscribed, Reuter reports from Taipei.
Underwriter Chiao Tung Bank said the shares, equal to 15 per cent of the
company's stock, were priced at TDollars 54 a share and would raise TDollars
972m (USDollars 36m). More than 1m applications were received, with 9,000
applicants awarded 2,000 shares each, said Chiao Tung.
The Taiwan government eventually plans to give up its majority stake in the
group. Chung Kuo is one of three state-owned companies, along with Chiao
Tung and Farmers Bank of China, that applied to list last year but postponed
the move because of a weak stock market.
A domestic and overseas flotation of shares in China Steel is planned for
early next year.
