FT  14 DEC 93 / Rover to raise car prices by 2.9%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN GRIFFITHS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The price of Rover cars is to rise by an average of 2.9 per cent from
Monday.
The increase, Rover's first for a year, is expected to be followed by other
manufacturers next month.
However, some of Rover's rivals indicated last night that the traditional
new year round of price increases - which has usually been triggered by
market leader Ford - may not materialise because of exceptionally
competitive conditions in the new car market.
Rover last increased its prices - also by an average of 2.9 per cent - last
December.
Ford prices have had a complex year. In January there were substantial
increases, mostly between 4.5 and 7.5 per cent. They were then cut by an
average of 5.2 per cent in April, though Ford increased them by an average
of 2.55 per cent in August.
Vauxhall imposed average increases of 2 per cent and 2.45 per cent in March
and August respectively. Peugeot has also put its prices up by a total of 3
per cent.
