FT  14 DEC 93 / Hanson to sell Bristol site
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Hanson, the Anglo-American conglomerate, has agreed to sell part of a
56-acre site in south Bristol as a campus for a further-education college.
This follows the failure to find a single purchaser for the site, which
incorporates one of Europe's largest air-conditioned factories.
The company plans to develop the site, once the headquarters of Imperial
Tobacco, which Hanson acquired in 1986, as a campus for South Bristol
College.
The factory will be demolished and replaced by an enterprise centre and a
non-food retail and leisure complex. Hanson estimates that the scheme will
cost up to Pounds 35m and that 1,200 jobs will be created.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
