FT  14 DEC 93 / World Trade News: Jakarta to buy Protons
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KIERAN COOKE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Indonesia plans to buy Malaysian-manufactured Proton cars in exchange for
Indonesian-made aircraft, reports Kieran Cooke.
Malaysia manufactures the Proton with Mitsubishi of Japan. Indonesia's
heavily subsidised Industri Pesawat Terbang Nusantara manufactures the
turboprop CN-235 aircraft with Casa of Spain.
